        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:59PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Nottely Dam, or 8 miles
west of Blairsville. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hemp, Nottely Dam, Ivy Log, Jones Creek, and Loving.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
